# Reserved Windows device name (NUL) — an untracked 0-byte/stray file created
# by a `2>nul` redirect cannot be deleted via Win32 path APIs because "nul"
# resolves to the NUL device. Keep it out of version control rather than risk
# it being committed.
nul
